                            <comment id="20308" author="vs" created="Fri, 16 Sep 2011 11:40:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the patch introduces a regression: &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=24540&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=24540&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the patch moved ldlm_namespace_unregister() from ldlm_namespace_free_post() to&lt;br/&gt;
ldlm_namespace_free_prior().&lt;br/&gt;
But it appears that in some cases ldlm_namespace_free_post() gets called alone without preceding&lt;br/&gt;
call to ldlm_namespace_free_prior() so that namespace does not get unregistered which hits LASSERT&lt;br/&gt;
in ldlm_namespace_free_post().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
